## Overview
This lab focused on bypassing strong input filters using Burp Suite Intruder.

## What I Learned
- How to enumerate allowed HTML tags
- How to test allowed attributes (event handlers)
- Why filters alone do not prevent XSS
- The importance of understanding execution context

## Tools Used
- Burp Suite (Intruder)
- Firefox DevTools

## Key Insight
Instead of guessing payloads, I used automation to identify what the application allowed, then built an attack based on those findings.

## Status
Concept mastered (lab environment issue prevented full exploit delivery)
